request.description:
### Get Academies

This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve a list of academies.

#### Request

The request does not require a request body. It simply makes a GET request to the specified endpoint.

- `base_url` (string): The base URL of the API.


#### Response

The response will be a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "academies": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "location": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "courses": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response will contain an array of academies, where each academy object will have an `id`, `name`, `location`, and a list of `courses`.

